In [17]:
# Categorizing and Segregatting arrival time and departure Time into Categories
def customize(time_str):
    time = pd.to_datetime(time_str).time()
    if time >= pd.to_datetime("04:00:00").time() and time < pd.to_datetime("11:59:59").time():
        return "Morning"
    elif time >= pd.to_datetime("12:00:00").time() and time < pd.to_datetime("16:59:59").time():
        return "Afternoon"
    elif time >= pd.to_datetime("17:00:00").time() and time <= pd.to_datetime("20:00:00").time():
        return "Evening"
    else:
        return "Night"

def fix_time_format(time_str):
    split = time_str.split(".")
    if len(split) == 2 and len(split[1]) == 1:
        return time_str + "0"
    else:                                           # EXTRACTING MINUTES AND HOURS 
        return time_str

df['time_tak'] = df['time_tak'].apply(fix_time_format)

for i in model:
    i.fit(X_train,y_train)

    print('Mean Squared Error (MSE):', round(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred),3))

    print('R2_score:', round(metrics.r2_score(y_test, y_pred),4))
    print("-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------")
    new_row = {'Model Name': i,
               'Mean_Absolute_Error_MAE' : metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred),
               'Root_Mean_Squared_Error_RMSE' : np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)),
               'Mean_Squared_Error_MSE' : metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred),
               'R2_score' : metrics.r2_score(y_test, y_pred)}
    a.append(new_row)
